This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and paraphrasing. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as these fields are closely related to NLP. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as paraphrasing is often used in search engines to improve query results. Finally, it could be classified under cs.SD (Sound) as it discusses transforming written language to spoken language.
